[Nouns] malediction, malison, curse, imprecation, denunciation, execration, anathema, ban, proscription, excommunication, commination, thunders of the Vatican, fulmination, maranatha; aspersion, disparagement, vilification, vituperation.
abuse; foul language, bad language, strong language, unparliamentary language; billingsgate, sauce, evil speaking; cursing; profane swearing, oath; foul invective, ribaldry, rude reproach, scurrility.
threat [more]; more bark than bite; invective (disapprobation) [more].
[Verbs] curse, accurse, imprecate, damn, swear at; curse with bell book and candle; invoke curses on the head of, call down curses on the head of; devote to destruction.
execrate, beshrew, scold; anathematize (censure) [more]; bold up to execration, denounce, proscribe, excommunicate, fulminate, thunder against; threaten [more].
curse and swear; swear, swear like a trooper; fall a cursing, rap out an oath, damn.
[Adjectives] cursing, cursed
